00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:48.381 position:50% align:center
all the mages in
town are in danger.

00:00:48.465 --> 00:00:49.966 position:50% align:center
This is terrifying.

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:52.719 position:50% align:center
Doesn't seem like a good time
to be a witch in this country.

00:00:52.802 --> 00:00:55.638 position:50% align:center
So, how to avoid
those annoying rogues?

00:00:57.849 --> 00:01:03.563 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA giggles] Perfect!
No one will recognize me

00:01:03.646 --> 00:01:05.732 position:50% align:center
as a mage in a cute
outfit like this one!

00:01:05.815 --> 00:01:08.651 position:50% align:center
I'm just your average,
everyday, beautiful woman!

00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:11.654 position:50% align:center
Yeah, a tourist
going sightseeing!

00:01:36.179 --> 00:01:39.307 position:50% align:center
[SAYA] United Magic Association
office, here I come!

00:01:39.391 --> 00:01:41.726 position:50% align:center
Gonna get this mission
over with, quick!

00:01:41.810 --> 00:01:43.269 position:50% align:center
Just gotta drop off
this little box

00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:44.479 position:50% align:center
and then collect the payment!

00:01:44.562 --> 00:01:46.356 position:50% align:center
Easy peazy lemon squeezy!

00:01:46.439 --> 00:01:47.732 position:50% align:center
Look, it's a witch!

00:01:47.816 --> 00:01:49.859 position:50% align:center
I wonder what she's doing here.

00:01:49.943 --> 00:01:52.987 position:50% align:center
And at a time like this. Wow.

00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:55.198 position:50% align:center
Why are all those people
down there staring at me?

00:01:55.281 --> 00:01:59.160 position:50% align:center
Oh! Because I'm so adorable
they can't help it, obviously!

00:02:01.996 --> 00:02:03.581 position:50% align:center
[yawns]

00:02:04.624 --> 00:02:06.751 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN]
Excuse me! Hello?

00:02:06.835 --> 00:02:08.253 position:50% align:center
Can you hear me?

00:02:08.336 --> 00:02:11.297 position:50% align:center
You up there, cute little
witch girl on the broom?

00:02:11.381 --> 00:02:12.924 position:50% align:center
[SAYA] I'm sorry,
I heard the word "cute,"

00:02:13.008 --> 00:02:14.676 position:50% align:center
so I assume you're
talking to me?

00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:17.887 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN]
Yes, indeed I am, my dear.

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:21.099 position:50% align:center
You see, some troublemakers
are on the loose in this town.

00:02:21.182 --> 00:02:23.351 position:50% align:center
They're especially drawn
to people wearing clothes

00:02:23.435 --> 00:02:25.145 position:50% align:center
like the ones you have on.

00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:27.022 position:50% align:center
Why, you could be
attacked at any moment

00:02:27.105 --> 00:02:28.148 position:50% align:center
if you're not careful!

00:02:28.231 --> 00:02:29.691 position:50% align:center
Are you sure about that?

00:02:29.774 --> 00:02:32.861 position:50% align:center
This doesn't seem like
a very dangerous town to me.

00:02:32.944 --> 00:02:35.488 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN] It's extremely
dangerous, I'm afraid.

00:02:35.572 --> 00:02:38.658 position:50% align:center
[SAYA] Wow, I had no idea
things were that bad.

00:02:38.742 --> 00:02:40.869 position:50% align:center
It must make living here
pretty awful, huh?

00:02:40.952 --> 00:02:42.620 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN] As an outsider,
you wouldn't know,

00:02:42.704 --> 00:02:44.748 position:50% align:center
but this town has
a history with mages.

00:02:44.831 --> 00:02:46.708 position:50% align:center
There've been attacks
in the past.

00:02:46.791 --> 00:02:48.376 position:50% align:center
Back in those days,
any poor sucker

00:02:48.460 --> 00:02:51.504 position:50% align:center
who could use magic was
shaking in their boots.

00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:52.756 position:50% align:center
What are you waiting for?

00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:54.632 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Huh?

00:02:54.716 --> 00:02:58.428 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN] Oh, don't mind him,
he was just praying! [laughs]

00:02:58.511 --> 00:03:01.389 position:50% align:center
Anyway, in order to stay safe
and survive the cruelties

00:03:01.473 --> 00:03:04.601 position:50% align:center
of this town, might I suggest
a helpful item from Curio--

00:03:04.684 --> 00:03:08.396 position:50% align:center
I mean the Antique Company's
wonderful self-defense set?

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.358 position:50% align:center
Ha-ha! I could tell you were up
to something with that spiel!

00:03:11.441 --> 00:03:15.403 position:50% align:center
Unfortunately, I turn down
all hard sells, so... Bye.

00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:17.530 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN]
No, wait, give me a minute!

00:03:18.615 --> 00:03:20.075 position:50% align:center
[growls]

00:03:30.502 --> 00:03:31.878 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Hm?

00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:35.882 position:50% align:center
I'm so sorry, ma'am.

00:03:35.965 --> 00:03:39.260 position:50% align:center
I really did try to get
that box, I swear.

00:03:39.344 --> 00:03:41.221 position:50% align:center
You're as useless
as ever, I see.

00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:43.765 position:50% align:center
It's my fault for
continuing to trust you.

00:03:43.848 --> 00:03:45.392 position:50% align:center
Time for a new plan.

00:03:45.475 --> 00:03:47.227 position:50% align:center
We don't actually have
to steal that box,

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:49.229 position:50% align:center
we just have to
get it open somehow.

00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:51.147 position:50% align:center
[cackles]

00:03:55.443 --> 00:03:57.362 position:50% align:center
--[DOG 11A growling]
--[CAT 11B growling]

00:03:57.445 --> 00:03:59.447 position:50% align:center
[barking]

00:04:03.451 --> 00:04:04.661 position:50% align:center
Okay, let's see.

00:04:04.744 --> 00:04:07.330 position:50% align:center
Pretty sure the
Association's over here.

00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:11.459 position:50% align:center
[SAYA yelps]

00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:22.178 position:50% align:center
[SAYA muffled grunting]

00:04:22.262 --> 00:04:23.138 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Is this it?

00:04:23.221 --> 00:04:25.265 position:50% align:center
Is this how I'm going to die?

00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:26.349 position:50% align:center
[GIRL]
Shut up!

00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.685 position:50% align:center
You can't let them hear you!

00:04:42.157 --> 00:04:44.909 position:50% align:center
Mina? How have you been?

00:04:46.786 --> 00:04:48.538 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:04:49.748 --> 00:04:51.833 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Wait. What are you doing here?

00:04:51.916 --> 00:04:54.669 position:50% align:center
[MINA] I'm doing undercover
work for the Association.

00:04:54.753 --> 00:04:58.548 position:50% align:center
There's a lot of deranged people
in this town causing trouble.

00:04:58.631 --> 00:05:00.216 position:50% align:center
I've been trying
to infiltrate them.

00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.510 position:50% align:center
Ooh, what kinda trouble?

00:05:02.594 --> 00:05:04.846 position:50% align:center
Why don't you tell me
why you're here first?

00:05:04.929 --> 00:05:06.389 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah, I'm on a job, too!

00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:09.476 position:50% align:center
Association!
Impressed, aren't'cha?

00:05:09.559 --> 00:05:12.812 position:50% align:center
[sighs] What's the
Association got you doing?

00:05:12.896 --> 00:05:14.939 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Just delivering this.

00:05:15.023 --> 00:05:15.815 position:50% align:center
[MINA]
What is it?

00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:17.275 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Iuhknow.

00:05:17.359 --> 00:05:18.902 position:50% align:center
I haven't heard anything
from the higher-ups

00:05:18.985 --> 00:05:20.528 position:50% align:center
about this though.

00:05:28.078 --> 00:05:29.704 position:50% align:center
Come on, let's go.

00:05:29.788 --> 00:05:31.748 position:50% align:center
You might as well stay
with me while you're here.

00:05:31.831 --> 00:05:34.209 position:50% align:center
Um, I still got a job
to do, remember?

00:05:34.292 --> 00:05:35.460 position:50% align:center
But don't worry about me!

00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:37.587 position:50% align:center
I'll just find an inn
after I drop this off!

00:05:37.671 --> 00:05:39.881 position:50% align:center
[sighs] Seriously?

00:05:39.964 --> 00:05:41.633 position:50% align:center
You know, a little bit
of happiness escapes

00:05:41.716 --> 00:05:42.884 position:50% align:center
every time you sigh.

00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:44.469 position:50% align:center
[growls]

00:05:44.552 --> 00:05:45.804 position:50% align:center
Uh--

00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:57.691 position:50% align:center
Just made this morning!
Buy one, get one!

00:06:05.657 --> 00:06:06.950 position:50% align:center
Was that the caf√©?

00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:08.576 position:50% align:center
It looks just like
the one where Foula

00:06:08.660 --> 00:06:10.829 position:50% align:center
met up with the
Curio Company boss!

00:06:13.331 --> 00:06:15.166 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA gasps]

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:18.586 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
I wonder which seat she sat in.

00:06:23.299 --> 00:06:25.010 position:50% align:center
[FANG]
I think that's our gal.

00:06:25.093 --> 00:06:26.344 position:50% align:center
[UNDERLING 10A]
Are you sure?

00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:28.179 position:50% align:center
She looks pretty
and plenty dumb.

00:06:28.263 --> 00:06:31.266 position:50% align:center
So, I'm sure she'll open that
box up without thinking twice.

00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:33.810 position:50% align:center
And then the real fun'll start.

00:06:33.893 --> 00:06:34.936 position:50% align:center
[FANG inhales]

00:06:36.855 --> 00:06:38.356 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.662 position:50% align:center
[MINA]
Listen to me, Sis.

00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:54.706 position:50% align:center
This is really important.

00:06:54.789 --> 00:06:58.960 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Who's that? Where am I?

00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:00.754 position:50% align:center
Wasn't I just at the caf√©?

00:07:00.837 --> 00:07:02.088 position:50% align:center
Those people I was
telling you about

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
are planning to attack
all the stores in town.

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.842 position:50% align:center
They're going to hit
jewelry shops,

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:07.635 position:50% align:center
weapon sellers, cloth merchants.

00:07:07.719 --> 00:07:10.263 position:50% align:center
No business here will be safe.

00:07:10.347 --> 00:07:12.891 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Is this a dream?

00:07:12.974 --> 00:07:14.934 position:50% align:center
Are you even listening to me?

00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.936 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Um, I'm sorry, but...

00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:20.148 position:50% align:center
I don't know who you are.
What's your name?

00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:21.900 position:50% align:center
Mi--

00:07:21.983 --> 00:07:25.403 position:50% align:center
You're not funny.
Stop joking around.

00:07:25.487 --> 00:07:26.946 position:50% align:center
I wasn't trying to make a joke,

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:28.365 position:50% align:center
and what's going
on with my voice?

00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:29.574 position:50% align:center
It sounds--

00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:42.253 position:50% align:center
What are you doing?

00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:50.387 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.097 position:50% align:center
No, don't! What if it's--

00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:53.181 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA gasps]

00:07:57.394 --> 00:08:02.273 position:50% align:center
[CROWD screaming]

00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:07.862 position:50% align:center
[MINA coughs]

00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:12.992 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Poisonous gas or something?

00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:16.454 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:16.538 --> 00:08:21.292 position:50% align:center
[BOTH panting]

00:08:22.544 --> 00:08:25.880 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:32.679 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:34.889 position:50% align:center
I guess I was so
surprised to see her again

00:08:34.973 --> 00:08:37.475 position:50% align:center
that I totally
forgot to breathe!

00:08:47.819 --> 00:08:50.113 position:50% align:center
Is that you, Miss Elaina?

00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:53.950 position:50% align:center
Hey, um. Are you okay?

00:08:55.952 --> 00:08:58.872 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I'm fine.

00:08:58.955 --> 00:09:00.373 position:50% align:center
Wait.

00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.877 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] You don't seem like
you're feeling very well.

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:06.171 position:50% align:center
Any fever? Let me feel.

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:08.298 position:50% align:center
Have you experienced any nausea?

00:09:09.424 --> 00:09:12.010 position:50% align:center
[MINA]
Huh? Get your hands off me!

00:09:12.093 --> 00:09:14.346 position:50% align:center
Was that really necessary?

00:09:14.429 --> 00:09:18.516 position:50% align:center
Uh-- Um, what's the matter?

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:20.435 position:50% align:center
Oh, my. Hello.

00:09:24.606 --> 00:09:26.399 position:50% align:center
So adorable.

00:09:28.902 --> 00:09:30.070 position:50% align:center
I love you.

00:09:30.153 --> 00:09:31.279 position:50% align:center
--[ELAINA] Thank you?
--You see the thing is,

00:09:31.363 --> 00:09:32.614 position:50% align:center
I never thought about
it quite like this,

00:09:32.697 --> 00:09:34.366 position:50% align:center
but I've loved you
my whole life.

00:09:34.449 --> 00:09:36.326 position:50% align:center
I know that sounds strange.

00:09:36.409 --> 00:09:37.786 position:50% align:center
I can't explain it,
but I miss you

00:09:37.869 --> 00:09:39.037 position:50% align:center
and think about you
all the time.

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:40.205 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Hold on.

00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:41.539 position:50% align:center
[MINA] Even though
you're older than me,

00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:43.375 position:50% align:center
you've always followed me
around and relied on me

00:09:43.458 --> 00:09:45.168 position:50% align:center
just like a lost little puppy.

00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:47.128 position:50% align:center
You make a pitiful big sister.

00:09:47.212 --> 00:09:48.838 position:50% align:center
You're so cute, though!

00:09:48.922 --> 00:09:50.548 position:50% align:center
Sometimes I just can't stand it!

00:09:50.632 --> 00:09:52.842 position:50% align:center
Whenever I look at you,
I just wanna pinch your cheeks

00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:55.845 position:50% align:center
and squish your
cute little face!

00:09:55.929 --> 00:09:57.722 position:50% align:center
It's true, and
also I don't think

00:09:57.806 --> 00:10:00.225 position:50% align:center
I need anybody else
in my life other than you!

00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:01.726 position:50% align:center
I apologize.

00:10:01.810 --> 00:10:04.604 position:50% align:center
I hate that I've always been
so cold to you despite that.

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:07.357 position:50% align:center
I really do love you
with my whole heart and soul.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:10.235 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry that I was never
honest about my feelings.

00:10:10.318 --> 00:10:12.070 position:50% align:center
I swear I could just
eat you right up!

00:10:12.153 --> 00:10:14.406 position:50% align:center
I love you, and I don't
know how to make it stop;

00:10:14.489 --> 00:10:16.116 position:50% align:center
these feelings are
so overwhelming!

00:10:16.199 --> 00:10:18.868 position:50% align:center
I've never felt love
like this before.

00:10:18.952 --> 00:10:21.955 position:50% align:center
I beg you, please love me back.

00:10:22.038 --> 00:10:23.665 position:50% align:center
You do, right?

00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:26.918 position:50% align:center
[thud]

00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:37.095 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:39.681 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
And up you go.

00:10:39.764 --> 00:10:43.184 position:50% align:center
My goodness. I wonder
what that was about.

00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.561 position:50% align:center
[CROWD chattering]

00:10:44.644 --> 00:10:46.229 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 11A]
Please wait!

00:10:47.647 --> 00:10:48.857 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 11B]
I love you so much!

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:51.067 position:50% align:center
[MAN 11A]
Leave me alone!

00:10:51.151 --> 00:10:52.652 position:50% align:center
[MAN 11C]
I can't help that I love you!

00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:55.030 position:50% align:center
[MAN 11D] But I'm in love with
your little brother, not you!

00:10:55.113 --> 00:10:57.532 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 11D] I'm sorry,
I just don't feel the same way!

00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:07.959 position:50% align:center
Everyone in town has
gone completely crazy.

00:11:08.043 --> 00:11:10.378 position:50% align:center
And I have a sneaking
suspicion that it has something

00:11:10.462 --> 00:11:12.672 position:50% align:center
to do with that strange
little box I opened.

00:11:12.756 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
--[SAYA panting] I love you!
--[ELAINA] That voice.

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:17.177 position:50% align:center
It sounds...

00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:19.346 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 11E]
Please stop!

00:11:19.429 --> 00:11:21.306 position:50% align:center
You don't know
what you're saying!

00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:23.183 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
You're so adorable!

00:11:23.266 --> 00:11:27.312 position:50% align:center
It doesn't matter the angle.
You get cuter by the second!

00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:29.647 position:50% align:center
No, that can't be possible.

00:11:29.731 --> 00:11:32.275 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Kiss me!

00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:34.778 position:50% align:center
It is. There's no
question that's me.

00:11:38.907 --> 00:11:41.284 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Is that you, Saya?

00:11:41.368 --> 00:11:43.203 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:43.286 --> 00:11:44.996 position:50% align:center
Hey, you're me.

00:11:46.539 --> 00:11:48.083 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:11:48.166 --> 00:11:52.003 position:50% align:center
[BOTH scream]

00:11:53.129 --> 00:11:55.632 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Huh? What is going on here?

00:11:55.715 --> 00:11:57.842 position:50% align:center
No part of this is
making any sense, Saya!

00:11:57.926 --> 00:12:00.053 position:50% align:center
Tell me what you did
and why you did it, now!

00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:02.138 position:50% align:center
I swear I don't know
what happened, either!

00:12:02.222 --> 00:12:03.723 position:50% align:center
I was doing a job
for the Association,

00:12:03.807 --> 00:12:05.475 position:50% align:center
and then out of nowhere,
I became Miss Elaina,

00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:07.560 position:50% align:center
only dressed even
cuter than usual!

00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:09.688 position:50% align:center
Something weird's going on
with the rest of the town, too.

00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:11.856 position:50% align:center
You can't think I'm behind that!

00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:14.067 position:50% align:center
Oh, I know you're not
responsible for them.

00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:15.485 position:50% align:center
I've got that part figured out.

00:12:15.568 --> 00:12:16.986 position:50% align:center
[sputters]

00:12:17.070 --> 00:12:20.031 position:50% align:center
A-hem. Now, if we could
return to the little matter

00:12:20.115 --> 00:12:21.491 position:50% align:center
of us switching bodies.

00:12:21.574 --> 00:12:23.034 position:50% align:center
Wait. What do you mean

00:12:23.118 --> 00:12:26.413 position:50% align:center
you figured out what's going on
with the crazy townspeople?

00:12:26.496 --> 00:12:29.541 position:50% align:center
Why don't we box that up
and set it aside for now.

00:12:29.624 --> 00:12:32.460 position:50% align:center
Speaking of boxes, I'm supposed
to have one with me.

00:12:32.544 --> 00:12:34.045 position:50% align:center
Do you know what happened to it?

00:12:34.129 --> 00:12:35.797 position:50% align:center
Whatever's inside it
is so dangerous,

00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.341 position:50% align:center
the box is never ever ever
supposed to be opened.

00:12:40.552 --> 00:12:42.470 position:50% align:center
[GIRL 11C]
Hey! Come back!

00:12:42.554 --> 00:12:44.305 position:50% align:center
[GUY 11C]
You can't catch me!

00:12:47.892 --> 00:12:50.937 position:50% align:center
Don't tell me you opened it!
That would be bad!

00:12:51.021 --> 00:12:54.482 position:50% align:center
Um, just a little?

00:12:54.566 --> 00:12:55.567 position:50% align:center
Are you serious?

00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:56.860 position:50% align:center
What in the world
were you thinking!

00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:59.154 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna be in so much trouble!

00:12:59.237 --> 00:13:02.991 position:50% align:center
You idiot! What the heck
is the matter with you, huh?

00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.994 position:50% align:center
Didn't my little sister
try to stop you?

00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:07.078 position:50% align:center
Your little sister?

00:13:07.162 --> 00:13:08.455 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah, the girl
who was with you,

00:13:08.538 --> 00:13:11.082 position:50% align:center
the super pretty one
with the long black hair.

00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:13.543 position:50% align:center
Ah. Oh, that girl.

00:13:15.837 --> 00:13:17.756 position:50% align:center
Why are you looking
at me like that?

00:13:17.839 --> 00:13:20.342 position:50% align:center
Let's just say that
you guys have, you know,

00:13:20.425 --> 00:13:21.760 position:50% align:center
a lot in common.

00:13:21.843 --> 00:13:23.261 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, what would
make you think that?

00:13:23.345 --> 00:13:25.638 position:50% align:center
We're totally different,
I promise!

00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:29.851 position:50% align:center
I'd appreciate it if you'd wipe

00:13:29.934 --> 00:13:32.145 position:50% align:center
that weird expression
off of my face.

00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:34.647 position:50% align:center
What are you talking about?

00:13:34.731 --> 00:13:36.358 position:50% align:center
Ah! Love!

00:13:36.441 --> 00:13:38.985 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:13:39.069 --> 00:13:41.821 position:50% align:center
Ugh, can you please get
away from the window?

00:13:41.905 --> 00:13:43.281 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
No way!

00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:46.534 position:50% align:center
I wanna be this close to you
all the time, Miss Elaina!

00:13:46.618 --> 00:13:48.745 position:50% align:center
I understand why you'd
feel that way, but our first

00:13:48.828 --> 00:13:50.997 position:50% align:center
priority should be finding
a way to get this city

00:13:51.081 --> 00:13:52.415 position:50% align:center
back to normal.

00:13:52.499 --> 00:13:54.209 position:50% align:center
Wait. Actually,
if it has to be

00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:56.586 position:50% align:center
somebody's priority,
then it should be mine.

00:13:56.670 --> 00:13:59.047 position:50% align:center
After all, I'm the dummy
who opened the stupid box.

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:01.383 position:50% align:center
Well, if that's the case,
since I'm still technically

00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.885 position:50% align:center
"you" at the moment, that means
I should probably help out, too,

00:14:03.968 --> 00:14:04.969 position:50% align:center
am I right?

00:14:05.053 --> 00:14:06.388 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Seriously, I'm going to need you

00:14:06.471 --> 00:14:07.931 position:50% align:center
to stop rubbing the window.

00:14:08.014 --> 00:14:11.685 position:50% align:center
So what kind of strange magic
was inside that box, anyway?

00:14:11.768 --> 00:14:13.687 position:50% align:center
I'd say that it's probably
more of a curse.

00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:16.356 position:50% align:center
It has the elements
of a strong love potion.

00:14:16.439 --> 00:14:18.316 position:50% align:center
Somebody must have
made us switch bodies

00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:20.944 position:50% align:center
so that you would
open it. Right?

00:14:21.027 --> 00:14:23.571 position:50% align:center
That seems like a pretty
sloppy plan to me.

00:14:23.655 --> 00:14:24.948 position:50% align:center
Yeah, true.

00:14:25.031 --> 00:14:27.742 position:50% align:center
What could they possibly
have hoped to accomplish?

00:14:27.826 --> 00:14:28.993 position:50% align:center
[UNDERLING 10A laughs]

00:14:29.077 --> 00:14:30.370 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:14:30.453 --> 00:14:32.205 position:50% align:center
[UNDERLING 10A] It's exactly
like the boss planned!

00:14:32.288 --> 00:14:34.916 position:50% align:center
A witch came here to deliver a
small box that was confiscated

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:36.876 position:50% align:center
in the past, thinking
it was a real job

00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:40.797 position:50% align:center
for the United Magic
Association, what an idiot!

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.091 position:50% align:center
Sure, I couldn't steal
the box from the witch,

00:14:43.174 --> 00:14:45.260 position:50% align:center
but then we switched the
witch's body with that simpleton

00:14:45.343 --> 00:14:48.013 position:50% align:center
of a girl, and she did
all the hard work for us!

00:14:48.096 --> 00:14:49.097 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:50.306 position:50% align:center
[UNDERLING 10A]
Thanks to her stupidity,

00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:53.184 position:50% align:center
everything's in chaos!
Go forth and steal!

00:14:53.268 --> 00:14:55.270 position:50% align:center
Before the smoke's
effects wear off!

00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:57.480 position:50% align:center
The Curio Company's back!

00:14:57.564 --> 00:15:01.443 position:50% align:center
And we've got years
of stealing to make up for!

00:15:04.195 --> 00:15:06.573 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] Hey, when I was talking
to your little sister earlier,

00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:08.742 position:50% align:center
she mentioned something about
a group that was planning

00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:10.660 position:50% align:center
an attack on the stores here.

00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:13.371 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Oh, you think that's them?

00:15:13.455 --> 00:15:16.124 position:50% align:center
He did say "the Curio
Company has been revived."

00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:18.626 position:50% align:center
The Curio whatchamuhoozit now?

00:15:18.710 --> 00:15:20.879 position:50% align:center
It's a chapter from the book,
<i>The Adventures of Nik√©</i> .

00:15:20.962 --> 00:15:22.881 position:50% align:center
Yeah, never read
that one, sorry.

00:15:22.964 --> 00:15:24.257 position:50% align:center
Of course not.

00:15:24.341 --> 00:15:26.259 position:50% align:center
Anyway, it's still
a really sloppy plan,

00:15:26.343 --> 00:15:28.261 position:50% align:center
but at least we know
what's going on.

00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:38.355 position:50% align:center
[UNDERLING 10A] Uh. We're really
sorry if we got carried away.

00:15:38.438 --> 00:15:41.107 position:50% align:center
No worries, I'm not even
that upset, honestly.

00:15:41.191 --> 00:15:42.734 position:50% align:center
But in exchange for
not roasting you,

00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:44.778 position:50% align:center
you can tell me where
your leader is.

00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:49.949 position:50% align:center
[GANG gasps, whimpers]

00:15:50.033 --> 00:15:52.327 position:50% align:center
[GANG screams]

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:54.871 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] After a totally
harmless conversation,

00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:57.791 position:50% align:center
the man told us what he knew
of the Curio Company's leader,

00:15:57.874 --> 00:16:00.335 position:50% align:center
and her exact location.

00:16:00.418 --> 00:16:02.504 position:50% align:center
I just don't understand
how you got the better of us,

00:16:02.587 --> 00:16:04.089 position:50% align:center
it was the perfect scheme.

00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:07.300 position:50% align:center
No, your plan was sloppy
and wreckless, at best.

00:16:07.384 --> 00:16:09.260 position:50% align:center
That's weird, 'cause earlier
you seemed pretty upset

00:16:09.344 --> 00:16:11.805 position:50% align:center
that they'd tricked
you, 'member?

00:16:11.888 --> 00:16:13.306 position:50% align:center
You misheard me.

00:16:13.390 --> 00:16:15.725 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I can't believe
I got the chance to capture

00:16:15.809 --> 00:16:17.602 position:50% align:center
the same exact
Curio Company leader

00:16:17.686 --> 00:16:19.979 position:50% align:center
that was in
<i>The Adventures of Nik√©!</i>

00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:21.648 position:50% align:center
[FANG grumbles]

00:16:21.731 --> 00:16:22.816 position:50% align:center
Okay, listen up.

00:16:22.899 --> 00:16:24.359 position:50% align:center
What do we have to do
in order to fix

00:16:24.442 --> 00:16:26.528 position:50% align:center
all of this body
switching nonsense?

00:16:26.611 --> 00:16:27.904 position:50% align:center
What do you mean by "we"?

00:16:27.987 --> 00:16:30.532 position:50% align:center
I'm totally fine if we don't
switch back, like, ever!

00:16:30.615 --> 00:16:32.784 position:50% align:center
And the sooner you can
make it happen, the better.

00:16:32.867 --> 00:16:35.412 position:50% align:center
I can't actually
do it right away.

00:16:35.495 --> 00:16:37.163 position:50% align:center
[growls]

00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:40.291 position:50% align:center
But they should go back to
normal in about a day or so!

00:16:40.375 --> 00:16:42.794 position:50% align:center
And you're absolutely
positive about that?

00:16:42.877 --> 00:16:45.672 position:50% align:center
[FANG]
Mm-hm. However!

00:16:45.755 --> 00:16:46.923 position:50% align:center
[SAYA, ELAINA]
Now what?

00:16:47.007 --> 00:16:49.175 position:50% align:center
Don't go celebratin'
your win just yet!

00:16:49.259 --> 00:16:51.136 position:50% align:center
The Curio Company is huge!

00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:52.595 position:50% align:center
There's still a lot
of guys out there

00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:55.265 position:50% align:center
that you haven't
caught, so nyah!

00:16:55.348 --> 00:16:56.766 position:50% align:center
[BOTH growl]

00:16:56.850 --> 00:16:59.310 position:50% align:center
While you're both wastin'
your precious time on me,

00:16:59.394 --> 00:17:03.273 position:50% align:center
the chaos is multiplyin', and my
guys are stealin' everything!

00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:05.650 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Too bad for you,

00:17:05.734 --> 00:17:08.028 position:50% align:center
I guess that makes
you guys the losers!

00:17:08.111 --> 00:17:09.279 position:50% align:center
So what now?

00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:10.947 position:50% align:center
We'll have to find
and stop then.

00:17:11.031 --> 00:17:12.574 position:50% align:center
--Let's split up.
--[SHEILA] Nope.

00:17:12.657 --> 00:17:14.200 position:50% align:center
[SHEILA]
It's already handled.

00:17:14.284 --> 00:17:15.869 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:19.122 position:50% align:center
Miss Fran?

00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:21.124 position:50% align:center
Teach? Is that you?

00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.126 position:50% align:center
Sheila? She's your teacher?

00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:24.711 position:50% align:center
I suppose it's been a while.

00:17:24.794 --> 00:17:27.797 position:50% align:center
I haven't seen those fangs
since the last time.

00:17:27.881 --> 00:17:29.174 position:50% align:center
What?

00:17:29.257 --> 00:17:31.551 position:50% align:center
You're that bratty
apprentice who caught me.

00:17:31.634 --> 00:17:32.802 position:50% align:center
Apprentice?

00:17:32.886 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50% align:center
My, your fangs are
much smaller now.

00:17:35.305 --> 00:17:36.556 position:50% align:center
Been chewing rocks?

00:17:36.639 --> 00:17:37.724 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:17:37.807 --> 00:17:39.351 position:50% align:center
Don't worry about the
Curio Company guys

00:17:39.434 --> 00:17:41.269 position:50% align:center
wreaking havoc
on the town anymore.

00:17:41.353 --> 00:17:43.772 position:50% align:center
We took care of all
of them on our way in.

00:17:43.855 --> 00:17:47.275 position:50% align:center
Too bad, so sad. It looks
like you lost again.

00:17:47.359 --> 00:17:48.735 position:50% align:center
"Again"?

00:17:48.818 --> 00:17:49.903 position:50% align:center
Now then.

00:17:49.986 --> 00:17:51.363 position:50% align:center
Why don't you do us
a favor and tell us

00:17:51.446 --> 00:17:54.824 position:50% align:center
how to return the
townsfolk to normal?

00:17:54.908 --> 00:17:56.910 position:50% align:center
But I don't wanna.

00:18:04.918 --> 00:18:07.504 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Uh, what happened?

00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:26.648 position:50% align:center
Done. And with that,

00:18:26.731 --> 00:18:28.024 position:50% align:center
everything should
be back to normal.

00:18:28.108 --> 00:18:30.694 position:50% align:center
Wow, who knew it'd
be that simple?

00:18:30.777 --> 00:18:33.279 position:50% align:center
You still haven't explained
what happened to her.

00:18:35.782 --> 00:18:38.076 position:50% align:center
[MAN 11S] I told you
those witches were no good!

00:18:42.247 --> 00:18:43.665 position:50% align:center
About that box.

00:18:43.748 --> 00:18:44.833 position:50% align:center
It's only a suspicion,

00:18:44.916 --> 00:18:46.418 position:50% align:center
but could it possibly
be from an island

00:18:46.501 --> 00:18:48.670 position:50% align:center
far beyond the horizon?

00:18:48.753 --> 00:18:49.754 position:50% align:center
That's correct.

00:18:49.838 --> 00:18:51.047 position:50% align:center
Case and point:

00:18:51.131 --> 00:18:53.091 position:50% align:center
Miss Elaina knows
everything about everything.

00:18:54.718 --> 00:18:56.720 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
It makes sense, but I wonder.

00:18:56.803 --> 00:19:00.140 position:50% align:center
Was the item that switched me
and Saya also from that island?

00:19:05.186 --> 00:19:07.230 position:50% align:center
When you see a person
you like even a little bit,

00:19:07.313 --> 00:19:09.399 position:50% align:center
you can't act normal
around them anymore.

00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:11.568 position:50% align:center
But when you see someone
you really like or love,

00:19:11.651 --> 00:19:13.194 position:50% align:center
you become a desperate fool;

00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:15.613 position:50% align:center
that's the curse
that smoke carries.

00:19:15.697 --> 00:19:17.365 position:50% align:center
Oh, I get it.

00:19:18.366 --> 00:19:20.076 position:50% align:center
Whatever, who cares?

00:19:21.828 --> 00:19:24.497 position:50% align:center
Uh... A-hem. Miss Elaina?

00:19:24.581 --> 00:19:25.874 position:50% align:center
Yes, what is it?

00:19:25.957 --> 00:19:28.001 position:50% align:center
I've heard about you
a lot from Saya.

00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:30.628 position:50% align:center
She told me about how you
helped prepare her for the exam

00:19:30.712 --> 00:19:32.922 position:50% align:center
after I left and that you
later found each other again

00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:35.550 position:50% align:center
in another country.

00:19:35.633 --> 00:19:37.260 position:50% align:center
And what's worse is
she sounded so happy

00:19:37.344 --> 00:19:39.012 position:50% align:center
when she talked about it!

00:19:39.095 --> 00:19:42.057 position:50% align:center
Uh. So, Mina, not to
change the subject but...

00:19:42.140 --> 00:19:44.768 position:50% align:center
Why did you leave Saya
in the Land of Mages?

00:19:44.851 --> 00:19:46.811 position:50% align:center
She was pretty
depressed, you know.

00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.732 position:50% align:center
[SHEILA]
Oh, yeah, that one's on me.

00:19:50.815 --> 00:19:52.359 position:50% align:center
It's because I wanted
to start her training

00:19:52.442 --> 00:19:53.818 position:50% align:center
as a witch right away.

00:19:53.902 --> 00:19:56.363 position:50% align:center
I basically ordered her
to return to her homeland.

00:19:56.446 --> 00:19:57.530 position:50% align:center
So that's why.

00:19:57.614 --> 00:19:59.032 position:50% align:center
Wait, when you say training...

00:19:59.115 --> 00:20:01.785 position:50% align:center
It means I was actually
Mina's teacher, too.

00:20:01.868 --> 00:20:03.536 position:50% align:center
Surely you guys knew that?

00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.205 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
No, we didn't.

00:20:05.288 --> 00:20:08.667 position:50% align:center
Saya has a bit of a tendency
to depend on people, right?

00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:10.585 position:50% align:center
So I decided to
separate these two;

00:20:10.669 --> 00:20:13.254 position:50% align:center
you can't grow if you're
always around the same people.

00:20:13.338 --> 00:20:15.048 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I guess
that makes sense.

00:20:15.131 --> 00:20:17.550 position:50% align:center
I just assumed Mina
was tired of Saya.

00:20:17.634 --> 00:20:20.136 position:50% align:center
And went back home because
she was so annoyed.

00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:21.638 position:50% align:center
Quite the opposite actually,

00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:23.598 position:50% align:center
Mina wouldn't let me
hear the end of it.

00:20:23.682 --> 00:20:26.643 position:50% align:center
She shouted things like "Why'd
you make me leave my sister?"

00:20:26.726 --> 00:20:28.478 position:50% align:center
and "I'll never forgive
you for this!"

00:20:28.561 --> 00:20:31.147 position:50% align:center
I think she even
threatened to curse me.

00:20:31.231 --> 00:20:33.233 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, that's crazy.

00:20:34.901 --> 00:20:36.820 position:50% align:center
Are you surprised? Heh.

00:20:36.903 --> 00:20:38.363 position:50% align:center
Based on what
happened yesterday,

00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:40.949 position:50% align:center
it doesn't really seem
that unexpected at all.

00:20:41.032 --> 00:20:42.909 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:20:42.992 --> 00:20:44.119 position:50% align:center
Oh, scandalous!

00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:45.495 position:50% align:center
It makes you wonder
which one of these two

00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:46.871 position:50% align:center
is the clingy one, huh?

00:20:46.955 --> 00:20:48.957 position:50% align:center
Right! Let's talk
about something else!

00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:50.250 position:50% align:center
How's the weather?

00:20:50.333 --> 00:20:53.336 position:50% align:center
[ALL laugh]

00:20:57.424 --> 00:21:00.343 position:50% align:center
[SAYA] No, I don't wanna go, you
can't make me, ya big meanie!

00:21:00.427 --> 00:21:01.594 position:50% align:center
I'm not leaving!

00:21:01.678 --> 00:21:03.596 position:50% align:center
I wanna stay here forever
and go sightseeing

00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:06.182 position:50% align:center
with Miss Elaina every day!

00:21:06.266 --> 00:21:07.892 position:50% align:center
Stop acting like such a brat.

00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:09.686 position:50% align:center
You know we have
work waiting for us.

00:21:09.769 --> 00:21:11.146 position:50% align:center
Who cares? I'm gonna quit!

00:21:11.229 --> 00:21:13.064 position:50% align:center
I don't need this dumb,
boring ol' job anyway!

00:21:13.148 --> 00:21:14.399 position:50% align:center
[SHEILA]
How you gonna eat?

00:21:14.482 --> 00:21:16.443 position:50% align:center
I'll just marry Miss Elaina
and she'll feed me!

00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:18.611 position:50% align:center
Uh. No thank you, I'll pass.

00:21:18.695 --> 00:21:20.071 position:50% align:center
You heard the lady.

00:21:20.155 --> 00:21:22.198 position:50% align:center
Come on. Let's get going.

00:21:23.366 --> 00:21:24.701 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
If looks could kill!

00:21:24.784 --> 00:21:26.786 position:50% align:center
Her glare is a curse
all by itself.

00:21:26.870 --> 00:21:28.288 position:50% align:center
See ya soon, Fran.

00:21:28.371 --> 00:21:31.332 position:50% align:center
Yep! In another year.

00:21:31.416 --> 00:21:36.379 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Leave me. Please.

00:21:36.463 --> 00:21:41.509 position:50% align:center
I want Miss Elaina!

00:21:41.593 --> 00:21:43.636 position:50% align:center
It would appear that
you're very loved.

00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:46.014 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah, I guess
you could say that.

00:21:48.224 --> 00:21:49.142 position:50% align:center
So, Elaina?

00:21:49.225 --> 00:21:50.643 position:50% align:center
Yes, Miss Fran?

00:21:50.727 --> 00:21:53.772 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you must've
realized it by now.

00:21:53.855 --> 00:21:55.523 position:50% align:center
Realized what?

00:21:55.607 --> 00:21:58.026 position:50% align:center
You've figured out who
my teacher was, haven't you?

00:21:58.109 --> 00:22:01.071 position:50% align:center
Your teacher? I don't think so.

00:22:01.154 --> 00:22:02.697 position:50% align:center
You know, when it comes
to the important things,

00:22:02.781 --> 00:22:03.948 position:50% align:center
you haven't changed.

00:22:04.032 --> 00:22:06.534 position:50% align:center
Like how you can't be
honest with yourself.

00:22:06.618 --> 00:22:09.537 position:50% align:center
For the record, I don't have
any problems with who I am.

00:22:09.621 --> 00:22:11.790 position:50% align:center
That's admirable, but you
will have to address it

00:22:11.873 --> 00:22:13.249 position:50% align:center
sooner or later.

00:22:13.333 --> 00:22:15.919 position:50% align:center
Maybe I will, but I'm not
ready to stop traveling yet.

00:22:16.002 --> 00:22:20.048 position:50% align:center
There are a lot of countries
I still want to visit.

00:22:20.131 --> 00:22:21.216 position:50% align:center
I'll live my life

00:22:21.299 --> 00:22:26.179 position:50% align:center
doing the things I want
at my own leisure.

00:22:26.262 --> 00:22:28.765 position:50% align:center
I'm just afraid that
if I were to truly

00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:31.601 position:50% align:center
put it all together,

00:22:31.685 --> 00:22:33.728 position:50% align:center
then maybe my days
of traveling freely

00:22:33.812 --> 00:22:35.855 position:50% align:center
would never be the same again.

00:22:37.357 --> 00:22:40.110 position:50% align:center
Listen, no matter who has
influenced you and your choices

00:22:40.193 --> 00:22:43.488 position:50% align:center
in this life, or whether
you know that person,

00:22:43.571 --> 00:22:46.533 position:50% align:center
you will always be Elaina,
the Ashen Witch.

00:22:46.616 --> 00:22:48.201 position:50% align:center
Do you really think so?

00:22:48.284 --> 00:22:49.411 position:50% align:center
[FRAN]
I'm certain.

00:22:49.494 --> 00:22:51.788 position:50% align:center
Did you know? My teacher
always seemed like

00:22:51.871 --> 00:22:53.957 position:50% align:center
she calculated everything,
but the truth is

00:22:54.040 --> 00:22:56.418 position:50% align:center
she was a pretty
carefree individual.

00:22:56.501 --> 00:22:57.711 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Seriously?

00:22:57.794 --> 00:22:59.921 position:50% align:center
[FRAN] Just like you're
a carefree individual.

00:23:00.005 --> 00:23:01.673 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
I don't understand.

00:23:01.756 --> 00:23:04.175 position:50% align:center
I guess what I'm saying is,
there's no reason

00:23:04.259 --> 00:23:07.220 position:50% align:center
for you to worry about every
little thing in this life.

00:23:07.303 --> 00:23:09.014 position:50% align:center
That said, I do
hope that one day

00:23:09.097 --> 00:23:11.933 position:50% align:center
you'll find the time to go back
to your home for a visit.

00:23:12.017 --> 00:23:14.686 position:50% align:center
Yes. One day.

00:23:14.769 --> 00:23:16.354 position:50% align:center
Don't forget, okay?

00:23:16.438 --> 00:23:17.689 position:50% align:center
And remember,

00:23:17.772 --> 00:23:19.774 position:50% align:center
you're always in our
thoughts and hearts, Elaina.

00:23:19.858 --> 00:23:20.734 position:50% align:center
We'll always love you.

00:23:20.817 --> 00:23:22.861 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:23:22.944 --> 00:23:24.237 position:50% align:center
Well, in that case...

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.322 position:50% align:center
...I guess I should say...

00:23:26.406 --> 00:23:28.616 position:50% align:center
...that I love you,
too, Miss Fran.

00:23:28.700 --> 00:23:31.077 position:50% align:center
Everyone in my life.

00:23:31.161 --> 00:23:32.454 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:23:35.707 --> 00:23:37.417 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Take care!

